WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.206 align:middle line:90%
[ Silence ]

00:00:06.206 --> 00:00:15.281 align:middle line:90%
[ Music ]

00:00:25.292 --> 00:00:26.393 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa Garr: Hi.

00:00:26.393 --> 00:00:29.329 align:middle line:84%
I'm Lisa Garr, host
of Gaiam Inspirations.

00:00:29.329 --> 00:00:30.497 align:middle line:90%
Over half a million people

00:00:30.497 --> 00:00:32.799 align:middle line:84%
in the US are burdened
with Crohn's disease.

00:00:32.799 --> 00:00:34.768 align:middle line:84%
And my guest today
was one of them.

00:00:34.768 --> 00:00:37.737 align:middle line:84%
However, Mee McCormick
decided to fight back

00:00:37.737 --> 00:00:41.174 align:middle line:84%
when this debilitating disease
almost cost her her entire

00:00:41.174 --> 00:00:44.444 align:middle line:84%
quality of life and
left her near dead.

00:00:44.444 --> 00:00:47.380 align:middle line:84%
Well, today in her new
book "My Kitchen Cure",

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:49.249 align:middle line:84%
she shares her amazing
discoveries

00:00:49.249 --> 00:00:51.051 align:middle line:90%
on the healing power of food.

00:00:51.051 --> 00:00:55.889 align:middle line:84%
And out of her plight, Mee also
became a TV cooking personality

00:00:55.889 --> 00:00:59.426 align:middle line:84%
and she's created a lifestyle
that will help anyone suffering

00:00:59.426 --> 00:01:02.329 align:middle line:84%
from any form of
autoimmune disease.

00:01:02.329 --> 00:01:03.964 align:middle line:84%
Welcome. Thank you
for being here.

00:01:03.964 --> 00:01:05.165 align:middle line:90%
>> Tracy McCormick: Thank you.

00:01:05.165 --> 00:01:06.833 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Oh my goodness,
you have so much to share.

00:01:06.833 --> 00:01:09.302 align:middle line:84%
Such a huge message,
I'm so glad you're here.

00:01:09.302 --> 00:01:10.237 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: I-- you know I'm

00:01:10.237 --> 00:01:11.671 align:middle line:84%
so glad I'm here
too in many ways.

00:01:11.671 --> 00:01:12.439 align:middle line:90%
Thanks.

00:01:12.439 --> 00:01:13.673 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yes, absolutely.

00:01:13.673 --> 00:01:15.509 align:middle line:84%
So, all right, tell me a
little bit about how it was

00:01:15.509 --> 00:01:17.511 align:middle line:90%
when you were growing up.

00:01:17.511 --> 00:01:18.645 align:middle line:90%
Where did you grow up?

00:01:18.645 --> 00:01:20.180 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I grow up
in-- well, I was born--

00:01:20.180 --> 00:01:23.617 align:middle line:84%
I'm Appalachian, so I was
born in Appalachian Mountains.

00:01:23.617 --> 00:01:26.686 align:middle line:84%
And then my mother
moved to Ohio and I grew

00:01:26.686 --> 00:01:28.655 align:middle line:84%
up in a little town
called Oberlin.

00:01:28.655 --> 00:01:31.491 align:middle line:84%
And Oberlin was a
super liberal--

00:01:31.491 --> 00:01:34.261 align:middle line:84%
is a super liberal arts
community and we move there

00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:35.729 align:middle line:84%
because she was--
became a single mother.

00:01:35.729 --> 00:01:38.131 align:middle line:84%
And there was a strong
women's community.

00:01:38.131 --> 00:01:41.500 align:middle line:90%
And we lived in a very poor part

00:01:41.500 --> 00:01:45.138 align:middle line:84%
of town predominantly
African-American part of town.

00:01:45.138 --> 00:01:47.374 align:middle line:84%
And it was just one of
those stories, you know,

00:01:47.374 --> 00:01:51.577 align:middle line:84%
late '70s early '80s, food
stamps, single parent.

00:01:51.577 --> 00:01:54.748 align:middle line:84%
She worked two jobs because
she had an autoimmune disease.

00:01:54.748 --> 00:01:55.815 align:middle line:90%
She had Crohn's disease.

00:01:55.815 --> 00:01:57.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Oh, she had
the disease as well.

00:01:57.450 --> 00:02:00.687 align:middle line:84%
So, you're working
with her having this.

00:02:00.687 --> 00:02:03.190 align:middle line:84%
But did she have the
awareness at all about food?

00:02:03.190 --> 00:02:04.324 align:middle line:90%
What types of foods, I mean--

00:02:04.324 --> 00:02:05.458 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: She had
zero awareness of food.

00:02:05.458 --> 00:02:06.660 align:middle line:90%
She--

00:02:06.660 --> 00:02:07.594 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Because she
didn't have a lot of choice.

00:02:07.594 --> 00:02:08.528 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: It
is the early '80s.

00:02:08.528 --> 00:02:11.298 align:middle line:84%
She was one of the
first people--

00:02:11.298 --> 00:02:13.300 align:middle line:84%
still in that wave of
first, sort of looking

00:02:13.300 --> 00:02:14.634 align:middle line:90%
at autoimmune disease.

00:02:14.634 --> 00:02:16.970 align:middle line:84%
I'm not even certain if
they knew it was autoimmune,

00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:18.772 align:middle line:90%
I'm not certain about anything

00:02:18.772 --> 00:02:21.540 align:middle line:84%
because I was just a little
girl watching her suffer.

00:02:21.540 --> 00:02:22.542 align:middle line:90%
She was in and out

00:02:22.542 --> 00:02:25.612 align:middle line:84%
of the Cleveland
Clinic and it was awful.

00:02:25.612 --> 00:02:27.180 align:middle line:90%
And she barely ate.

00:02:27.180 --> 00:02:29.516 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And you have-- we
have a picture here of some

00:02:29.516 --> 00:02:31.818 align:middle line:84%
of the food that you
did eat at that time.

00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:32.919 align:middle line:90%
We can take a look at this--

00:02:32.919 --> 00:02:33.753 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:02:33.753 --> 00:02:34.321 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: It consisted of, what?

00:02:34.321 --> 00:02:35.722 align:middle line:90%
We had Spam--

00:02:35.722 --> 00:02:40.126 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Spam, chipped ham,
ketchup, white bread, macaroni

00:02:40.126 --> 00:02:42.495 align:middle line:84%
and cheese, and I
had a dairy allergy.

00:02:42.495 --> 00:02:45.899 align:middle line:84%
Just minimal food, my
mother's family is Italian.

00:02:45.899 --> 00:02:49.035 align:middle line:84%
And so, we always had a
tomato sauce and pasta.

00:02:49.035 --> 00:02:51.304 align:middle line:84%
It was inexpensive and a pot
of sauce would go a week.

00:02:51.304 --> 00:02:53.173 align:middle line:84%
But we just didn't
have access to food

00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:55.508 align:middle line:84%
because we lived
in a food desert.

00:02:55.508 --> 00:02:59.579 align:middle line:84%
So, the combination of
no car, no bus system,

00:02:59.579 --> 00:03:03.884 align:middle line:84%
no public transportation and no
money and a sick mother who is

00:03:03.884 --> 00:03:06.386 align:middle line:84%
in and out of work
meant no food.

00:03:06.386 --> 00:03:08.154 align:middle line:90%
Food was an issue.

00:03:08.154 --> 00:03:10.457 align:middle line:84%
I was hungry most
of my childhood.

00:03:10.457 --> 00:03:11.858 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:03:11.858 --> 00:03:14.094 align:middle line:84%
This is a picture here of what
your food cabinet looked like.

00:03:14.094 --> 00:03:16.596 align:middle line:84%
I think we have here, is this--
where did you get all these--

00:03:16.596 --> 00:03:18.698 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: That was-- what
happens is when you're a child

00:03:18.698 --> 00:03:21.801 align:middle line:84%
and a person who doesn't
have money and access to food

00:03:21.801 --> 00:03:24.638 align:middle line:84%
and then you grow up and
you earn your own money.

00:03:24.638 --> 00:03:26.940 align:middle line:84%
You-- and you get
food, what do you do?

00:03:26.940 --> 00:03:29.175 align:middle line:84%
You buy all the foods
that you couldn't have.

00:03:29.175 --> 00:03:30.543 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh, OK.

00:03:30.543 --> 00:03:32.646 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, I became a
food hoarder like most people.

00:03:32.646 --> 00:03:34.414 align:middle line:90%
If I had food in my kitchen,

00:03:34.414 --> 00:03:36.516 align:middle line:84%
then we had food,
then we were OK.

00:03:36.516 --> 00:03:38.151 align:middle line:84%
And so, my husband
would complain and say,

00:03:38.151 --> 00:03:40.387 align:middle line:84%
"You buy all these food
and we don't even eat it

00:03:40.387 --> 00:03:41.754 align:middle line:90%
and we throw it away."

00:03:41.754 --> 00:03:42.956 align:middle line:90%
But I had to have it.

00:03:42.956 --> 00:03:46.192 align:middle line:84%
And I actually was obsessed
with processed food.

00:03:46.192 --> 00:03:49.195 align:middle line:84%
Because believe it or
not, my mother wasn't

00:03:49.195 --> 00:03:52.032 align:middle line:84%
such a processed food
person, we didn't have money.

00:03:52.032 --> 00:03:54.000 align:middle line:84%
So, processed food at
the time was expensive,

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:55.402 align:middle line:90%
it's changed, now it's cheaper.

00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:56.569 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah, yeah.

00:03:56.569 --> 00:03:58.104 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: But we
didn't have money for it.

00:03:58.104 --> 00:04:00.573 align:middle line:84%
So, when I did have money
and earn my own money

00:04:00.573 --> 00:04:03.443 align:middle line:84%
and had a family of my own,
I became a food hoarder.

00:04:03.443 --> 00:04:06.446 align:middle line:84%
I just had anything in a box,
I shop by the picture, so.

00:04:06.446 --> 00:04:07.480 align:middle line:90%
[ Laugh ]

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:08.581 align:middle line:90%
With all the pictures.

00:04:08.581 --> 00:04:10.850 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Oh that looks
good, that's pretty.

00:04:10.850 --> 00:04:13.753 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: That's
the way I saw it.

00:04:13.753 --> 00:04:15.155 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So, you
then took this--

00:04:15.155 --> 00:04:17.223 align:middle line:84%
all these foods that you're
eating and you got sicker

00:04:17.223 --> 00:04:19.192 align:middle line:84%
as an adult than
you were as a child?

00:04:19.192 --> 00:04:21.227 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: When I was
born, I'm an interesting case.

00:04:21.227 --> 00:04:24.197 align:middle line:84%
I was born and I had something
called an intussusception.

00:04:24.197 --> 00:04:28.401 align:middle line:84%
And that meant my intestines
were born sort-- were formed--

00:04:28.401 --> 00:04:30.203 align:middle line:90%
they collapsed on themselves.

00:04:30.203 --> 00:04:33.873 align:middle line:84%
And then I found out later
when I got the test results

00:04:33.873 --> 00:04:36.476 align:middle line:84%
from the labs as an
adult, I researched

00:04:36.476 --> 00:04:40.747 align:middle line:84%
and contacted the hospital
that I had an ulceration

00:04:40.747 --> 00:04:43.917 align:middle line:84%
which is said not to be
true that you can't be born

00:04:43.917 --> 00:04:46.853 align:middle line:84%
with an ulceration in your
intestines, but I was.

00:04:46.853 --> 00:04:51.024 align:middle line:84%
So, I had an operation the day I
was born to-- like a resection.

00:04:51.024 --> 00:04:52.358 align:middle line:84%
They removed part
of my intestines

00:04:52.358 --> 00:04:54.260 align:middle line:90%
and connected them again.

00:04:54.260 --> 00:04:56.730 align:middle line:84%
And I was a very sickly
child and I had a lot

00:04:56.730 --> 00:04:58.865 align:middle line:84%
of food sensitivities
and food allergies.

00:04:58.865 --> 00:05:02.936 align:middle line:84%
But we were too poor to
shop for different kids.

00:05:02.936 --> 00:05:05.438 align:middle line:84%
And so, I had to eat
what I was allergic to

00:05:05.438 --> 00:05:07.507 align:middle line:90%
and eat what I was sensitive to.

00:05:07.507 --> 00:05:08.608 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: So, OK.

00:05:08.608 --> 00:05:10.777 align:middle line:84%
So, you moved out of
that and you got married

00:05:10.777 --> 00:05:11.845 align:middle line:90%
and where did you live?

00:05:11.845 --> 00:05:12.946 align:middle line:84%
Where did you live
when you got married?

00:05:12.946 --> 00:05:14.180 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I got
married and we lived

00:05:14.180 --> 00:05:16.249 align:middle line:90%
in Nashville, on a ranch.

00:05:16.249 --> 00:05:17.617 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:05:17.617 --> 00:05:19.853 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: We lived on a
cattle ranch which is amazing.

00:05:19.853 --> 00:05:20.987 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:05:20.987 --> 00:05:21.955 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: In a way we'll
getting to that story

00:05:21.955 --> 00:05:23.456 align:middle line:84%
because in a way
it saved your life.

00:05:23.456 --> 00:05:24.491 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:05:24.491 --> 00:05:25.558 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: But in the
interim you moved

00:05:25.558 --> 00:05:27.394 align:middle line:84%
to the jungle, why
did you do that?

00:05:27.394 --> 00:05:28.528 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Well,

00:05:28.528 --> 00:05:29.896 align:middle line:84%
what happened is we were
leaving in two places.

00:05:29.896 --> 00:05:32.365 align:middle line:84%
We were living in LA because
my husband had a project in LA

00:05:32.365 --> 00:05:35.769 align:middle line:84%
and I was a writer, and we
also lived in Nashville.

00:05:35.769 --> 00:05:38.371 align:middle line:84%
And then he finished his
project in LA and we said,

00:05:38.371 --> 00:05:39.906 align:middle line:84%
"We're not going to
keep living here."

00:05:39.906 --> 00:05:41.241 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:05:41.241 --> 00:05:42.342 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And it was before
my daughter started school

00:05:42.342 --> 00:05:44.244 align:middle line:84%
and I really wanted
to write a book.

00:05:44.244 --> 00:05:47.347 align:middle line:84%
I had this dream all of
my life to write a book.

00:05:47.347 --> 00:05:49.149 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it wasn't even
just a dream as much

00:05:49.149 --> 00:05:51.618 align:middle line:84%
as it was a conversation
with myself

00:05:51.618 --> 00:05:53.219 align:middle line:84%
that I was going
to write a book.

00:05:53.219 --> 00:05:56.389 align:middle line:84%
So, I had a plan to write a
book called the "Adventures

00:05:56.389 --> 00:05:58.391 align:middle line:90%
of Princess Know It All".

00:05:58.391 --> 00:06:01.394 align:middle line:84%
And I-- we decided let's
have a grand adventure,

00:06:01.394 --> 00:06:03.463 align:middle line:84%
we'll go to the jungle,
we'll pack our babies.

00:06:03.463 --> 00:06:06.199 align:middle line:84%
My baby was one and
my other one was five.

00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:10.503 align:middle line:84%
And we'll-- Lee love to
surf and I love Mexico.

00:06:10.503 --> 00:06:12.906 align:middle line:84%
So, we rented a house
in Mexico closed up--

00:06:12.906 --> 00:06:14.741 align:middle line:84%
shut everything down
in LA and moved

00:06:14.741 --> 00:06:16.709 align:middle line:84%
to a little town called
Sayulita in the mouth

00:06:16.709 --> 00:06:18.978 align:middle line:84%
of the jungle, right
on the beach.

00:06:18.978 --> 00:06:20.013 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And it was
beautiful there.

00:06:20.013 --> 00:06:20.580 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: It was amazing.

00:06:20.580 --> 00:06:21.514 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:06:21.514 --> 00:06:22.816 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And
I took an office

00:06:22.816 --> 00:06:24.918 align:middle line:84%
and I got my work ethic back
and I started writing the

00:06:24.918 --> 00:06:26.820 align:middle line:84%
"Adventures of Princess
Know It All."

00:06:26.820 --> 00:06:28.421 align:middle line:90%
And I started a blog.

00:06:28.421 --> 00:06:33.626 align:middle line:84%
And that blog actually spun
me into writing for magazines

00:06:33.626 --> 00:06:35.395 align:middle line:90%
because the blog was picked up.

00:06:35.395 --> 00:06:37.931 align:middle line:84%
And I really was
on this adventure.

00:06:37.931 --> 00:06:39.098 align:middle line:90%
But then--

00:06:39.098 --> 00:06:41.034 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Well, what
time-- what year was that?

00:06:41.034 --> 00:06:42.869 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: This
was six years ago.

00:06:42.869 --> 00:06:44.003 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Six years ago.

00:06:44.003 --> 00:06:45.004 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Everything
has been happening fast.

00:06:45.004 --> 00:06:46.039 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: My goodness.

00:06:46.039 --> 00:06:47.340 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Life
changed in a minute.

00:06:47.340 --> 00:06:48.842 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: But then, OK, so we
have a picture here of you

00:06:48.842 --> 00:06:50.210 align:middle line:90%
in the jungle and you writing--

00:06:50.210 --> 00:06:51.144 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:06:51.144 --> 00:06:52.479 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: -- and enjoying
yourself.

00:06:52.479 --> 00:06:55.248 align:middle line:84%
But you were still at that
point very unaware that you were

00:06:55.248 --> 00:06:56.349 align:middle line:90%
as sick as you were, right?

00:06:56.349 --> 00:06:57.550 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Well,
I would think that at

00:06:57.550 --> 00:07:00.487 align:middle line:84%
about 25 years old, I
suffered my first bowel--

00:07:00.487 --> 00:07:01.888 align:middle line:90%
partial bowel obstruction.

00:07:01.888 --> 00:07:03.923 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is
everything stops flowing

00:07:03.923 --> 00:07:05.425 align:middle line:90%
through the digestive tract.

00:07:05.425 --> 00:07:08.728 align:middle line:84%
Blood, nothing moves, they shut
down, there's inflammation.

00:07:08.728 --> 00:07:10.497 align:middle line:90%
It begins to close.

00:07:10.497 --> 00:07:13.600 align:middle line:84%
It's like having-- it's like a
heart attack in your intestines,

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:14.934 align:middle line:90%
like, you can feel it.

00:07:14.934 --> 00:07:16.069 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:07:16.069 --> 00:07:16.903 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: You can
feel everything stops.

00:07:16.903 --> 00:07:17.403 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:07:17.403 --> 00:07:18.438 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:07:18.438 --> 00:07:19.372 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And
so-- and you feel it

00:07:19.372 --> 00:07:21.541 align:middle line:84%
from the abdomen
down to your feet.

00:07:21.541 --> 00:07:25.178 align:middle line:84%
And I had my first
bowel obstruction at 25.

00:07:25.178 --> 00:07:27.780 align:middle line:84%
And went to the hospital and
they thought I had scar tissue

00:07:27.780 --> 00:07:29.249 align:middle line:90%
from the surgery at birth.

00:07:29.249 --> 00:07:30.884 align:middle line:84%
And that's what they
thought it was.

00:07:30.884 --> 00:07:34.287 align:middle line:84%
And then after that, I
started to get a burn

00:07:34.287 --> 00:07:35.722 align:middle line:90%
in my stomach, in my abdomen.

00:07:35.722 --> 00:07:38.257 align:middle line:90%
And that burn was radiated.

00:07:38.257 --> 00:07:40.360 align:middle line:84%
And so, really what it
was was just this common

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:42.896 align:middle line:90%
digestive distress.

00:07:42.896 --> 00:07:45.598 align:middle line:84%
You know, had a-- I started
to form a relationship

00:07:45.598 --> 00:07:48.001 align:middle line:84%
with not feeling
well after I ate.

00:07:48.001 --> 00:07:50.370 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Which you're talking
for most people right now.

00:07:50.370 --> 00:07:53.640 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Most people right
now have gas bloating pressure.

00:07:53.640 --> 00:07:54.908 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Burning.

00:07:54.908 --> 00:07:57.343 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Discomfort,
burning all of the above.

00:07:57.343 --> 00:07:59.312 align:middle line:84%
And so, I was one
of those people.

00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:00.613 align:middle line:90%
And it just continued.

00:08:00.613 --> 00:08:02.916 align:middle line:84%
And then I would have
another partial obstruction,

00:08:02.916 --> 00:08:04.083 align:middle line:90%
go back to the hospital.

00:08:04.083 --> 00:08:05.919 align:middle line:84%
They pumped my stomach
through my nose.

00:08:05.919 --> 00:08:07.720 align:middle line:90%
It was awful, it was traumatic--

00:08:07.720 --> 00:08:08.955 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:08:08.955 --> 00:08:09.789 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And they
would say, "Well that's all,

00:08:09.789 --> 00:08:11.791 align:middle line:90%
you just had inflammation."

00:08:11.791 --> 00:08:15.895 align:middle line:84%
But no one ever really thought
that it could be anything else.

00:08:15.895 --> 00:08:21.034 align:middle line:84%
So, then when we were living in
the jungle, the radiating pain--

00:08:21.034 --> 00:08:23.403 align:middle line:84%
I mean I talk about
it and I remember it

00:08:23.403 --> 00:08:24.771 align:middle line:90%
and it's just a nightmare.

00:08:24.771 --> 00:08:27.974 align:middle line:84%
And it became horrible to the
point where I couldn't eat.

00:08:27.974 --> 00:08:30.777 align:middle line:84%
And the bowel obstructions
were happening more and more.

00:08:30.777 --> 00:08:32.378 align:middle line:90%
So, we came back to LA..

00:08:32.378 --> 00:08:33.079 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah

00:08:33.079 --> 00:08:33.880 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: For test.

00:08:33.880 --> 00:08:34.580 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:08:34.580 --> 00:08:34.981 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh, you did.

00:08:34.981 --> 00:08:35.647 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:08:35.647 --> 00:08:36.950 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: I did.

00:08:36.950 --> 00:08:38.450 align:middle line:84%
I left the jungle because I
had a terrible obstruction

00:08:38.450 --> 00:08:41.955 align:middle line:84%
and my husband was in the
United States, I was alone.

00:08:41.955 --> 00:08:46.459 align:middle line:84%
We lived in a heavily
narco area of the jungle.

00:08:46.459 --> 00:08:49.729 align:middle line:84%
Meaning the narcos were
fighting for control.

00:08:49.729 --> 00:08:51.631 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Oh, that part
of Mexico is not safe.

00:08:51.631 --> 00:08:54.434 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, it wasn't
safe and I had an obstruction

00:08:54.434 --> 00:08:56.102 align:middle line:90%
at night on a Saturday.

00:08:56.102 --> 00:08:58.571 align:middle line:84%
I had a housekeeper that
would come on Mondays.

00:08:58.571 --> 00:09:00.440 align:middle line:90%
But it was Saturday and no one

00:09:00.440 --> 00:09:02.875 align:middle line:84%
in the jungle really knew
me to come and save me.

00:09:02.875 --> 00:09:03.643 align:middle line:90%
So, I was--

00:09:03.643 --> 00:09:04.744 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: So, no one-- oh,

00:09:04.744 --> 00:09:06.679 align:middle line:84%
so you stayed there
first for several days.

00:09:06.679 --> 00:09:08.815 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: In pain with two
babies and I couldn't move.

00:09:08.815 --> 00:09:10.016 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:09:10.016 --> 00:09:11.317 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, I knew
I had to get out of there

00:09:11.317 --> 00:09:12.285 align:middle line:90%
or I was going to die there.

00:09:12.285 --> 00:09:13.486 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yes.

00:09:13.486 --> 00:09:16.789 align:middle line:84%
And so, when you came and
we have a picture here

00:09:16.789 --> 00:09:20.793 align:middle line:84%
of what you looked like at that
point and you were pretty thin.

00:09:20.793 --> 00:09:22.261 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: 89 pounds.

00:09:22.261 --> 00:09:23.396 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: 89 pounds.

00:09:23.396 --> 00:09:24.697 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: 89 pounds.

00:09:24.697 --> 00:09:26.499 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: This is a picture
of your face at that point.

00:09:26.499 --> 00:09:27.333 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:09:27.333 --> 00:09:28.468 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: When was this taken?

00:09:28.468 --> 00:09:31.871 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I think
that picture was taken

00:09:31.871 --> 00:09:35.541 align:middle line:84%
about believe it or not
maybe four years ago.

00:09:35.541 --> 00:09:37.744 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow, wow, wow.

00:09:37.744 --> 00:09:38.411 align:middle line:90%
And look at you now.

00:09:38.411 --> 00:09:39.812 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:09:39.812 --> 00:09:41.414 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Well, we're going to
get to that part but what was--

00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:43.216 align:middle line:84%
and something that you
pointed out for me here

00:09:43.216 --> 00:09:45.251 align:middle line:84%
in this picture was
the fear in your face.

00:09:45.251 --> 00:09:46.586 align:middle line:90%
And people go through this.

00:09:46.586 --> 00:09:49.155 align:middle line:84%
When you have digestive issues,
you don't know what to do,

00:09:49.155 --> 00:09:51.224 align:middle line:84%
there's no band aid
you can put on it.

00:09:51.224 --> 00:09:52.558 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Well,
there is no band aid

00:09:52.558 --> 00:09:54.927 align:middle line:84%
and you can't see
it from the outside.

00:09:54.927 --> 00:09:56.162 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right.

00:09:56.162 --> 00:09:57.196 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And it's
with any invisible disease,

00:09:57.196 --> 00:09:59.332 align:middle line:90%
any type of chronic disease.

00:09:59.332 --> 00:10:00.433 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: True.

00:10:00.433 --> 00:10:01.734 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And the
fear that I had was

00:10:01.734 --> 00:10:04.137 align:middle line:90%
because my mother died at 39.

00:10:04.137 --> 00:10:07.106 align:middle line:84%
And I was devastated
by her loss.

00:10:07.106 --> 00:10:08.207 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh yeah.

00:10:08.207 --> 00:10:09.542 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: My mom
was an amazing person.

00:10:09.542 --> 00:10:12.545 align:middle line:84%
And when she died,
it left a hole

00:10:12.545 --> 00:10:14.347 align:middle line:90%
in my heart as a young girl.

00:10:14.347 --> 00:10:17.583 align:middle line:84%
And when I got as sick as
her, I thought, "Oh no,

00:10:17.583 --> 00:10:19.419 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to leave my girls."

00:10:19.419 --> 00:10:20.653 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:10:20.653 --> 00:10:23.756 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And that fear,
you know, getting well,

00:10:23.756 --> 00:10:26.125 align:middle line:84%
the next phase of my
life from getting well.

00:10:26.125 --> 00:10:31.264 align:middle line:84%
Before I could even begin to
get well, I had to sort of move

00:10:31.264 --> 00:10:34.100 align:middle line:84%
that blanket of black
butterfly that surround me.

00:10:34.100 --> 00:10:36.369 align:middle line:84%
I mean I was swarmed
with the fear of death.

00:10:36.369 --> 00:10:37.403 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Constantly.

00:10:37.403 --> 00:10:38.738 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Constantly,
constantly.

00:10:38.738 --> 00:10:42.341 align:middle line:84%
I mean it just I would fall
into tears in a conversation

00:10:42.341 --> 00:10:44.310 align:middle line:84%
because I just knew
I was leaving.

00:10:44.310 --> 00:10:46.079 align:middle line:90%
And I was going to leave them.

00:10:46.079 --> 00:10:49.614 align:middle line:84%
And it because I had
experienced that type of loss,

00:10:49.614 --> 00:10:52.118 align:middle line:90%
it shook me to my core.

00:10:52.118 --> 00:10:53.786 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So, how did
you get out of that?

00:10:53.786 --> 00:10:55.154 align:middle line:90%
How did you--

00:10:55.154 --> 00:10:58.958 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I-- well, when
I embarked on my food journey,

00:10:58.958 --> 00:11:02.662 align:middle line:84%
I also started working with
a cabalistic acupuncturist

00:11:02.662 --> 00:11:04.731 align:middle line:90%
who happen to pray a lot.

00:11:04.731 --> 00:11:08.167 align:middle line:84%
And he would put needles in
me and he would talk to me.

00:11:08.167 --> 00:11:10.403 align:middle line:90%
And he would talk to me each--

00:11:10.403 --> 00:11:12.839 align:middle line:84%
he was a very interesting
acupuncturist

00:11:12.839 --> 00:11:20.046 align:middle line:84%
because each needle represented
for me like a past experience.

00:11:20.046 --> 00:11:24.016 align:middle line:84%
Not a past life as in before
this life but a past life

00:11:24.016 --> 00:11:26.252 align:middle line:84%
within this life, so
something that it happened.

00:11:26.252 --> 00:11:26.753 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: In this life.

00:11:26.753 --> 00:11:27.854 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:11:27.854 --> 00:11:28.721 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And his
needles would go in,

00:11:28.721 --> 00:11:30.323 align:middle line:90%
and I would have a memory.

00:11:30.323 --> 00:11:33.359 align:middle line:84%
I would have a memory
of my father leaving.

00:11:33.359 --> 00:11:36.229 align:middle line:84%
A memory of not being
good enough as a teenager.

00:11:36.229 --> 00:11:38.864 align:middle line:84%
A memory of an abusive
relationship.

00:11:38.864 --> 00:11:42.068 align:middle line:84%
A memory of when I was an
abusive person in my life

00:11:42.068 --> 00:11:44.537 align:middle line:84%
because we've been
abusive at some point.

00:11:44.537 --> 00:11:45.371 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:11:45.371 --> 00:11:46.339 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: And this is normal step

00:11:46.339 --> 00:11:47.707 align:middle line:84%
that people go through
a lifetime--

00:11:47.707 --> 00:11:49.041 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Regular steps,
nothing like-- traumatic.

00:11:49.041 --> 00:11:50.409 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:11:50.409 --> 00:11:51.844 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Just, you know,
when I wasn't as positive--

00:11:51.844 --> 00:11:52.678 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Kind person.

00:11:52.678 --> 00:11:53.246 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: -- as a person.

00:11:53.246 --> 00:11:54.313 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah

00:11:54.313 --> 00:11:55.148 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: -- or
kind as I could be.

00:11:55.148 --> 00:11:56.649 align:middle line:90%
And so, each needle was attached

00:11:56.649 --> 00:11:59.485 align:middle line:84%
to a judgment of
my self or fear.

00:11:59.485 --> 00:12:02.121 align:middle line:84%
And overtime, I would
lay on his table

00:12:02.121 --> 00:12:05.158 align:middle line:84%
and I would just fall
sleep into these memories.

00:12:05.158 --> 00:12:07.927 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Is that
where you started to--

00:12:07.927 --> 00:12:11.264 align:middle line:84%
what you really think
contributed to the fire

00:12:11.264 --> 00:12:14.767 align:middle line:84%
in the belly, the gut,
the inflammation one

00:12:14.767 --> 00:12:17.403 align:middle line:84%
of these negative
memories and thoughts

00:12:17.403 --> 00:12:19.005 align:middle line:84%
that you hold on
to unconsciously?

00:12:19.005 --> 00:12:20.873 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Yeah, I think
that they become the burdens--

00:12:20.873 --> 00:12:21.707 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:12:21.707 --> 00:12:22.308 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: -- that we carry.

00:12:22.308 --> 00:12:23.009 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:12:23.009 --> 00:12:24.210 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: And our--

00:12:24.210 --> 00:12:26.612 align:middle line:84%
you know, our root of our
body is our intestines.

00:12:26.612 --> 00:12:28.281 align:middle line:90%
And if the root of the--

00:12:28.281 --> 00:12:30.983 align:middle line:84%
of a tree, the trees
roots are their core.

00:12:30.983 --> 00:12:32.819 align:middle line:84%
And if a tree's roots
are poisoned

00:12:32.819 --> 00:12:34.854 align:middle line:84%
or toxic then the
tree goes down.

00:12:34.854 --> 00:12:36.222 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing.

00:12:36.222 --> 00:12:39.525 align:middle line:84%
And so, you know, we really
pack around all of our sadness.

00:12:39.525 --> 00:12:42.929 align:middle line:84%
And I packed it and held it
tightly in my intestines.

00:12:42.929 --> 00:12:44.230 align:middle line:90%
And-- so that was--

00:12:44.230 --> 00:12:46.699 align:middle line:84%
I've actually really talked
about it this way before.

00:12:46.699 --> 00:12:47.767 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: It makes so
much sense though.

00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:48.835 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I've
never talk about him,

00:12:48.835 --> 00:12:51.003 align:middle line:84%
his name is Gil Ben-Ami,
he's in Nashville.

00:12:51.003 --> 00:12:53.539 align:middle line:84%
And it means happy son
of my people in Hebrew.

00:12:53.539 --> 00:12:54.173 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Wow.

00:12:54.173 --> 00:12:55.141 align:middle line:90%
That was his name?

00:12:55.141 --> 00:12:55.775 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Yeah,
his name is Gil.

00:12:55.775 --> 00:12:57.076 align:middle line:90%
He's still there.

00:12:57.076 --> 00:12:59.111 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: But it-- the act
of what you went through was

00:12:59.111 --> 00:13:02.248 align:middle line:84%
so important because they
led you to solutions.

00:13:02.248 --> 00:13:03.216 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:13:03.216 --> 00:13:04.617 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: I mean that
was [inaudible].

00:13:04.617 --> 00:13:06.419 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I mean that was
my first action of like what was

00:13:06.419 --> 00:13:10.723 align:middle line:84%
that really did is I got
to see that being a child

00:13:10.723 --> 00:13:15.094 align:middle line:84%
of a sick parent or
an unwell person,

00:13:15.094 --> 00:13:17.930 align:middle line:90%
it physically affects you.

00:13:17.930 --> 00:13:21.601 align:middle line:84%
Children are deeply
affected by all of the adults

00:13:21.601 --> 00:13:23.502 align:middle line:84%
that are suffering
chronic disease.

00:13:23.502 --> 00:13:25.605 align:middle line:84%
And I had a lot of things
I knew that hurt me.

00:13:25.605 --> 00:13:28.774 align:middle line:84%
The loss of my father, the
loss of this, the heartache

00:13:28.774 --> 00:13:32.011 align:middle line:84%
over relationships,
but I had never looked

00:13:32.011 --> 00:13:37.049 align:middle line:84%
at my mother's suffering and
how it influenced my fears

00:13:37.049 --> 00:13:38.084 align:middle line:90%
in my future.

00:13:38.084 --> 00:13:41.120 align:middle line:84%
Until that moment on
that man's stable.

00:13:41.120 --> 00:13:43.089 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And so, when you
started to move all of that,

00:13:43.089 --> 00:13:46.459 align:middle line:84%
and started to release all
that which I'm sure took--

00:13:46.459 --> 00:13:47.426 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:13:47.426 --> 00:13:48.861 align:middle line:84%
Actually it's pretty
fast with him.

00:13:48.861 --> 00:13:50.463 align:middle line:84%
Because I would go
three times a week

00:13:50.463 --> 00:13:52.965 align:middle line:84%
because the other side
effect of acupuncture

00:13:52.965 --> 00:13:56.302 align:middle line:84%
and healing the digestive
tract is it helps with pain.

00:13:56.302 --> 00:13:57.403 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh.

00:13:57.403 --> 00:13:58.604 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, I
would have less pain.

00:13:58.604 --> 00:14:00.473 align:middle line:84%
And I would just
get on his table.

00:14:00.473 --> 00:14:02.208 align:middle line:84%
When I would go with
the memories

00:14:02.208 --> 00:14:03.776 align:middle line:90%
and they had the therapist--

00:14:03.776 --> 00:14:04.911 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Well, yeah.

00:14:04.911 --> 00:14:05.478 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Because
I had to talk about it.

00:14:05.478 --> 00:14:06.679 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:14:06.679 --> 00:14:08.080 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I was like,
I have to find somebody

00:14:08.080 --> 00:14:11.784 align:middle line:84%
to help me process who I've been
so that I can clean it all up.

00:14:11.784 --> 00:14:14.654 align:middle line:84%
You know, I want to be my
next greatest version on me--

00:14:14.654 --> 00:14:15.888 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:14:15.888 --> 00:14:16.722 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: -- and how
I'm going to clean that up?

00:14:16.722 --> 00:14:17.723 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: That's what leaders do.

00:14:17.723 --> 00:14:18.991 align:middle line:90%
Now you moved yourself

00:14:18.991 --> 00:14:21.460 align:middle line:84%
into finding whole
foods, and finding--

00:14:21.460 --> 00:14:22.795 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:14:22.795 --> 00:14:24.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: -- foods that actually
started to heal your body.

00:14:24.130 --> 00:14:25.898 align:middle line:90%
How did you get to these foods?

00:14:25.898 --> 00:14:27.833 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, like sort of
all happened at the same time.

00:14:27.833 --> 00:14:29.168 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK

00:14:29.168 --> 00:14:30.403 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I meet Gil, I
left the jungle because we--

00:14:30.403 --> 00:14:33.039 align:middle line:84%
the doctors had found a
hole in my small intestine.

00:14:33.039 --> 00:14:35.474 align:middle line:84%
And it was the total
circumference and it meant

00:14:35.474 --> 00:14:38.077 align:middle line:84%
that I have been hemorrhaging
for many years slowly.

00:14:38.077 --> 00:14:42.014 align:middle line:84%
I was completely anemic, I
was on Iron transfusions.

00:14:42.014 --> 00:14:44.784 align:middle line:84%
We were-- they were
searching me for cancer.

00:14:44.784 --> 00:14:46.252 align:middle line:90%
And they couldn't find any.

00:14:46.252 --> 00:14:49.855 align:middle line:84%
And the last chance was to
do a biopsy of the whole.

00:14:49.855 --> 00:14:54.193 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't well enough
to undergo that procedure.

00:14:54.193 --> 00:14:56.595 align:middle line:90%
And so, at the same time,

00:14:56.595 --> 00:14:59.265 align:middle line:84%
I was back in Nashville,
I was with doctors.

00:14:59.265 --> 00:15:02.301 align:middle line:84%
I was seeing the Acupuncturist
because I believe in supporting.

00:15:02.301 --> 00:15:03.436 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:15:03.436 --> 00:15:04.136 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: You know,
you got to do it both.

00:15:04.136 --> 00:15:05.237 align:middle line:90%
You got to do it all.

00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:06.706 align:middle line:84%
You can't make one right
and the other wrong.

00:15:06.706 --> 00:15:07.540 align:middle line:90%
You got to work as a team.

00:15:07.540 --> 00:15:08.641 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: That's great point.

00:15:08.641 --> 00:15:09.308 align:middle line:90%
Great point.

00:15:09.308 --> 00:15:10.509 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:15:10.509 --> 00:15:12.378 align:middle line:84%
And then, I connected to
woman name Virginia Harper

00:15:12.378 --> 00:15:13.779 align:middle line:90%
who is in Nashville.

00:15:13.779 --> 00:15:15.815 align:middle line:90%
Half the year lives in Spain.

00:15:15.815 --> 00:15:18.784 align:middle line:84%
I have found a book
in Mexico online.

00:15:18.784 --> 00:15:20.586 align:middle line:84%
But you can't get
mail on the jungle.

00:15:20.586 --> 00:15:23.723 align:middle line:84%
And the book that I found online
was about this woman who lived

00:15:23.723 --> 00:15:26.492 align:middle line:84%
in Maine, who would
heal their body.

00:15:26.492 --> 00:15:28.160 align:middle line:84%
Well, a good friend
of mine in Nashville,

00:15:28.160 --> 00:15:31.297 align:middle line:84%
Maryalice Kirchdoerffer who
