>> Lisa: But you found the book

00:15:49.114 --> 00:15:50.649 align:middle line:84%
and you found your
way towards foods.

00:15:50.649 --> 00:15:51.150 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: I did.

00:15:51.150 --> 00:15:52.518 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:15:52.518 --> 00:15:54.387 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And this is-- this is
a picture here that you have

00:15:54.387 --> 00:15:56.789 align:middle line:84%
of all the different diets
that you had tried, right?

00:15:56.789 --> 00:15:57.790 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:15:57.790 --> 00:15:58.491 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: You went
through all these.

00:15:58.491 --> 00:15:59.425 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Oh yeah.

00:15:59.425 --> 00:16:00.626 align:middle line:84%
I started out with
Virginia Harper

00:16:00.626 --> 00:16:02.395 align:middle line:84%
who is predominantly a
macrobiotic counselor.

00:16:02.395 --> 00:16:03.396 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:16:03.396 --> 00:16:04.764 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: It
taught me the basics.

00:16:04.764 --> 00:16:07.666 align:middle line:84%
It was a beautiful place to
start because it's old school--

00:16:07.666 --> 00:16:08.667 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:16:08.667 --> 00:16:09.235 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: --
simple, simple cooking.

00:16:09.235 --> 00:16:10.536 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right.

00:16:10.536 --> 00:16:11.570 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And it's and
you have-- you get skilled.

00:16:11.570 --> 00:16:13.339 align:middle line:84%
I mean you really
learn how to cook--

00:16:13.339 --> 00:16:14.707 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: That where you
got all your skills, OK.

00:16:14.707 --> 00:16:16.342 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I got
main skills there,

00:16:16.342 --> 00:16:17.710 align:middle line:84%
but then that wasn't
enough for me.

00:16:17.710 --> 00:16:19.478 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to know what
the Maker's Diet was,

00:16:19.478 --> 00:16:20.679 align:middle line:90%
what the Gerson diet was.

00:16:20.679 --> 00:16:23.649 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to understand
all of the-- I wanted to--

00:16:23.649 --> 00:16:25.384 align:middle line:90%
I was looking for my thread.

00:16:25.384 --> 00:16:27.820 align:middle line:84%
I needed to find the
string that connected it all

00:16:27.820 --> 00:16:31.424 align:middle line:84%
because there isn't just
one way to wellness.

00:16:31.424 --> 00:16:34.693 align:middle line:84%
And one way isn't going
to keep you well either.

00:16:34.693 --> 00:16:36.028 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: What is
the thread then?

00:16:36.028 --> 00:16:37.129 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: The
thread is real food.

00:16:37.129 --> 00:16:37.897 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Real food.

00:16:37.897 --> 00:16:38.931 align:middle line:90%
OK, and that's what you--

00:16:38.931 --> 00:16:39.899 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Unadulterated
real food.

00:16:39.899 --> 00:16:40.599 align:middle line:90%
No chemicals--

00:16:40.599 --> 00:16:41.367 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Whole food.

00:16:41.367 --> 00:16:42.635 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Whole food.

00:16:42.635 --> 00:16:45.738 align:middle line:84%
Food in its whole forms,
simply prepared, no chemicals,

00:16:45.738 --> 00:16:48.841 align:middle line:84%
no additives, no
preservatives in rotation.

00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:50.242 align:middle line:90%
You must rotate your food.

00:16:50.242 --> 00:16:53.279 align:middle line:84%
If you do not rotate your
food, you'll create an excess.

00:16:53.279 --> 00:16:56.114 align:middle line:84%
And in that excess is
where the imbalance lies.

00:16:56.114 --> 00:16:59.051 align:middle line:84%
And the-- and the illness
will just creep back in

00:16:59.051 --> 00:17:00.719 align:middle line:90%
or a new one will find its way.

00:17:00.719 --> 00:17:03.288 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So, you've obviously
you've educated yourself a lot.

00:17:03.288 --> 00:17:05.691 align:middle line:84%
About food and about
the body as well--

00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.093 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:17:07.093 --> 00:17:07.927 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: -- and then we have a
side here that you put together

00:17:07.927 --> 00:17:09.028 align:middle line:90%
about knowing your intestines--

00:17:09.028 --> 00:17:10.095 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:17:10.095 --> 00:17:10.895 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Did you learn
everything about--

00:17:10.895 --> 00:17:12.031 align:middle line:90%
I think that's a great idea.

00:17:12.031 --> 00:17:13.265 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Oh I think
it's a great idea too.

00:17:13.265 --> 00:17:14.999 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: We have them,
we all have intestines.

00:17:14.999 --> 00:17:17.103 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Yeah and
it's not taught in school.

00:17:17.103 --> 00:17:18.237 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:17:18.237 --> 00:17:19.772 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And you go
to gastroenterologist,

00:17:19.772 --> 00:17:21.739 align:middle line:84%
and they don't teach
you about them.

00:17:21.739 --> 00:17:24.509 align:middle line:84%
And so, suddenly this life
[inaudible] and I felt, wow,

00:17:24.509 --> 00:17:26.479 align:middle line:90%
I have a wound in my intestine.

00:17:26.479 --> 00:17:29.782 align:middle line:84%
And the only thing that's
touching it is food.

00:17:29.782 --> 00:17:32.151 align:middle line:84%
Why can't the food
become medicine?

00:17:32.151 --> 00:17:35.654 align:middle line:84%
Why wouldn't I-- if you have a
whole or scrape on your knee,

00:17:35.654 --> 00:17:37.189 align:middle line:90%
what do you would put on it?

00:17:37.189 --> 00:17:38.491 align:middle line:90%
You put medicine on it.

00:17:38.491 --> 00:17:41.460 align:middle line:84%
You don't add unhealthy
bacteria, do you?

00:17:41.460 --> 00:17:42.528 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right, right, right.

00:17:42.528 --> 00:17:43.863 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, if
you have a weakening

00:17:43.863 --> 00:17:48.367 align:middle line:84%
in your digestive tract, and
you don't heal it properly,

00:17:48.367 --> 00:17:49.768 align:middle line:90%
then what's going to happen?

00:17:49.768 --> 00:17:52.538 align:middle line:84%
Your entire-- again that's your
root, that's your tree's root,

00:17:52.538 --> 00:17:55.474 align:middle line:84%
that's your body's root if
the body is going to go down.

00:17:55.474 --> 00:17:57.209 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: So, you learned about
your intestine, I think that's--

00:17:57.209 --> 00:17:58.711 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I was--
and I wrote about it,

00:17:58.711 --> 00:18:00.212 align:middle line:90%
it's like know thy intestines.

00:18:00.212 --> 00:18:04.316 align:middle line:84%
If you have any sort of
health issues or imbalances,

00:18:04.316 --> 00:18:07.553 align:middle line:84%
understand that the only
way to bring balance is

00:18:07.553 --> 00:18:10.789 align:middle line:84%
in the small intestine because
that's where the villi are

00:18:10.789 --> 00:18:13.859 align:middle line:84%
that grab the nutrition,
that then funnel it

00:18:13.859 --> 00:18:16.729 align:middle line:84%
into the main vein, into the
liver, and into the blood.

00:18:16.729 --> 00:18:18.864 align:middle line:84%
And if those intestines
are not working,

00:18:18.864 --> 00:18:20.132 align:middle line:90%
you're never going to get well.

00:18:20.132 --> 00:18:21.534 align:middle line:84%
No matter how many
pills you take.

00:18:21.534 --> 00:18:24.737 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: But what about those
bad habits, those comfort foods,

00:18:24.737 --> 00:18:26.405 align:middle line:90%
those things that you need to--

00:18:26.405 --> 00:18:27.806 align:middle line:90%
I mean did that help you

00:18:27.806 --> 00:18:29.875 align:middle line:84%
to educate yourself
about the foods and--

00:18:29.875 --> 00:18:31.210 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:18:31.210 --> 00:18:32.545 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: -- intestines in
order to kick those bad habits?

00:18:32.545 --> 00:18:33.679 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: You know, I
think that's the whole thing.

00:18:33.679 --> 00:18:36.048 align:middle line:84%
I think that the more
that you go out there

00:18:36.048 --> 00:18:37.183 align:middle line:90%
and you seek information.

00:18:37.183 --> 00:18:38.884 align:middle line:84%
You know, my kitchen
cure is called

00:18:38.884 --> 00:18:41.353 align:middle line:84%
that because it was
my kitchen cure.

00:18:41.353 --> 00:18:43.155 align:middle line:90%
And it was how I got well.

00:18:43.155 --> 00:18:45.524 align:middle line:84%
But it's to inspire people
to find their own cure--

00:18:45.524 --> 00:18:46.492 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: That they
can do it, yeah.

00:18:46.492 --> 00:18:47.560 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: --
like ask questions.

00:18:47.560 --> 00:18:49.528 align:middle line:84%
Try things, see what
works in your body,

00:18:49.528 --> 00:18:50.963 align:middle line:90%
what doesn't work in your body.

00:18:50.963 --> 00:18:53.332 align:middle line:84%
And the more information
you have then you have a

00:18:53.332 --> 00:18:54.867 align:middle line:90%
consciousness going on.

00:18:54.867 --> 00:18:56.569 align:middle line:84%
And you're going
to make choices,

00:18:56.569 --> 00:18:58.771 align:middle line:90%
and then it's your choice.

00:18:58.771 --> 00:19:02.575 align:middle line:84%
That is a big deal
because we want on-- we--

00:19:02.575 --> 00:19:05.978 align:middle line:84%
our food stuff is
mega, mega, mega, mega,

00:19:05.978 --> 00:19:07.713 align:middle line:90%
mega, situation for us.

00:19:07.713 --> 00:19:09.915 align:middle line:84%
We have a situation
with our food

00:19:09.915 --> 00:19:12.084 align:middle line:84%
because we're super
sensitive to it.

00:19:12.084 --> 00:19:14.320 align:middle line:84%
You know, we're full of
our own self judgments,

00:19:14.320 --> 00:19:16.222 align:middle line:84%
we judge ourselves
what we feed ourselves,

00:19:16.222 --> 00:19:18.190 align:middle line:84%
what we feed our children,
what's in our refrigerator--

00:19:18.190 --> 00:19:19.024 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: We do have a lot of--

00:19:19.024 --> 00:19:20.226 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: -- what we eat.

00:19:20.226 --> 00:19:21.026 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: We have a lot of
conversation around food

00:19:21.026 --> 00:19:21.627 align:middle line:90%
in our own heads, don't we?

00:19:21.627 --> 00:19:22.928 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:19:22.928 --> 00:19:24.230 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I own drug and
alcohol treatment centers

00:19:24.230 --> 00:19:25.998 align:middle line:90%
and eating disorder clinics.

00:19:25.998 --> 00:19:27.333 align:middle line:90%
And the thing

00:19:27.333 --> 00:19:30.002 align:middle line:84%
about understanding how people
change, is how I changed.

00:19:30.002 --> 00:19:31.704 align:middle line:84%
I watched-- I have
watched people

00:19:31.704 --> 00:19:34.006 align:middle line:90%
for 12 years change their lives.

00:19:34.006 --> 00:19:37.843 align:middle line:84%
And shift their addictions and
change the story in their mind

00:19:37.843 --> 00:19:41.247 align:middle line:84%
about why they're not well
or why they do what they do.

00:19:41.247 --> 00:19:42.514 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: I see.

00:19:42.514 --> 00:19:43.716 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And I had to
apply that to my own life.

00:19:43.716 --> 00:19:46.118 align:middle line:84%
So, the food conversation
is a sensitive one.

00:19:46.118 --> 00:19:50.456 align:middle line:84%
And if we make foods bad,
then we're never going to--

00:19:50.456 --> 00:19:52.024 align:middle line:84%
we're not going to
influence anyone.

00:19:52.024 --> 00:19:53.225 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: So, you talk

00:19:53.225 --> 00:19:54.627 align:middle line:84%
about kicking those
habits in this other slide.

00:19:54.627 --> 00:19:57.329 align:middle line:84%
You talk about getting the
emotional support around it.

00:19:57.329 --> 00:19:59.198 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know that you-- those--

00:19:59.198 --> 00:20:00.266 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:20:00.266 --> 00:20:00.933 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: -- the food
clinics and-- the--

00:20:00.933 --> 00:20:01.734 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:20:01.734 --> 00:20:02.801 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: -- support centers.

00:20:02.801 --> 00:20:04.637 align:middle line:84%
Are they the same
things as the kitchens?

00:20:04.637 --> 00:20:05.638 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: No,
they're different.

00:20:05.638 --> 00:20:07.172 align:middle line:84%
They're-- we own
the Recovery Ranch.

00:20:07.172 --> 00:20:09.675 align:middle line:84%
Well, my husband started
the Recovery Ranch on--

00:20:09.675 --> 00:20:10.209 align:middle line:90%
in Nashville.

00:20:10.209 --> 00:20:11.543 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Oh.

00:20:11.543 --> 00:20:13.112 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And then we have
the Integrated Life Center

00:20:13.112 --> 00:20:15.547 align:middle line:84%
in Nashville and their
holistic approaches to drug

00:20:15.547 --> 00:20:18.183 align:middle line:84%
and alcohol addiction
and eating disorders.

00:20:18.183 --> 00:20:19.385 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:20:19.385 --> 00:20:21.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Healing addiction
through food as well.

00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:22.354 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And
healing addiction

00:20:22.354 --> 00:20:23.689 align:middle line:90%
through food is gigantic.

00:20:23.689 --> 00:20:25.758 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And of course
emotional addiction--

00:20:25.758 --> 00:20:27.426 align:middle line:84%
I mean healing through
emotions as well--

00:20:27.426 --> 00:20:29.061 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Well, it
all is connected, right?

00:20:29.061 --> 00:20:29.862 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yes, absolutely.

00:20:29.862 --> 00:20:31.063 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: It's all one.

00:20:31.063 --> 00:20:32.464 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: All right, so
you're steps to wellness.

00:20:32.464 --> 00:20:35.034 align:middle line:84%
And you kind of have five steps
here that you've laid out for us

00:20:35.034 --> 00:20:37.670 align:middle line:90%
in terms of steps to wellness.

00:20:37.670 --> 00:20:39.071 align:middle line:90%
Yes. OK.

00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:41.307 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: First thing you
want to do is you want to start

00:20:41.307 --> 00:20:45.044 align:middle line:84%
to pay attention to what
are your food sensitivities.

00:20:45.044 --> 00:20:45.978 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:20:45.978 --> 00:20:47.079 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And
the big things--

00:20:47.079 --> 00:20:48.647 align:middle line:84%
the first thing to do
is to pay attention

00:20:48.647 --> 00:20:51.517 align:middle line:84%
to what are you eating
all of the time.

00:20:51.517 --> 00:20:53.786 align:middle line:84%
So, you have to become
mindful of your food, you know.

00:20:53.786 --> 00:20:55.954 align:middle line:84%
You have to pay attention what
am I eating, what am I craving--

00:20:55.954 --> 00:20:57.156 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: So, you're saying--

00:20:57.156 --> 00:20:57.823 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: -- how many
times should I eat it.

00:20:57.823 --> 00:20:58.757 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Food diary?

00:20:58.757 --> 00:20:59.291 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Food
diary is great.

00:20:59.291 --> 00:21:00.392 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:21:00.392 --> 00:21:01.327 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And even
the simple like, oh,

00:21:01.327 --> 00:21:03.996 align:middle line:84%
I ate those corn
chips yesterday.

00:21:03.996 --> 00:21:07.333 align:middle line:84%
Oh, I have those corn
chips three days in a row.

00:21:07.333 --> 00:21:10.869 align:middle line:90%
Oh, you know, what am I doing?

00:21:10.869 --> 00:21:12.137 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:21:12.137 --> 00:21:13.505 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Just the
mindful, what am I feeding me,

00:21:13.505 --> 00:21:15.874 align:middle line:84%
and what is my child
eating everyday.

00:21:15.874 --> 00:21:17.576 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Yeah, That's
another huge part of it.

00:21:17.576 --> 00:21:19.845 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: A food journal
for your kids is a great idea.

00:21:19.845 --> 00:21:21.046 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: For them to do.

00:21:21.046 --> 00:21:21.847 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Now for
them to do, for you to do.

00:21:21.847 --> 00:21:24.016 align:middle line:90%
And you can do it with them.

00:21:24.016 --> 00:21:24.717 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: And make it fun.

00:21:24.717 --> 00:21:25.384 align:middle line:90%
So, it doesn't set up--

00:21:25.384 --> 00:21:26.218 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah--

00:21:26.218 --> 00:21:27.286 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: -- the whole addiction.

00:21:27.286 --> 00:21:28.120 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: -- you
can make a calendar

00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:30.389 align:middle line:90%
that says, Monday, we ate this.

00:21:30.389 --> 00:21:33.892 align:middle line:84%
And then the-- once you start
doing it, by the second week,

00:21:33.892 --> 00:21:38.030 align:middle line:84%
they go "Oh mama, we haven't
had this since last week."

00:21:38.030 --> 00:21:40.666 align:middle line:84%
That-- you don't think it sets
a-- you do it fun though, right?

00:21:40.666 --> 00:21:41.600 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:21:41.600 --> 00:21:42.167 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: You
don't make it--

00:21:42.167 --> 00:21:43.168 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:21:43.168 --> 00:21:44.169 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Or
nothing can be made bad,

00:21:44.169 --> 00:21:45.137 align:middle line:84%
and nothing can be
made restrictive.

00:21:45.137 --> 00:21:47.072 align:middle line:84%
It's not about what
you can't have.

00:21:47.072 --> 00:21:49.241 align:middle line:84%
It's about all the
things you can't have.

00:21:49.241 --> 00:21:50.743 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: You can have, right.

00:21:50.743 --> 00:21:52.010 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that's very important.

00:21:52.010 --> 00:21:54.947 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Changing the
can't to can is gigantic.

00:21:54.947 --> 00:21:56.348 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: I notice
that when I switch

00:21:56.348 --> 00:21:58.917 align:middle line:90%
to the gluten-free lifestyle.

00:21:58.917 --> 00:22:00.018 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:22:00.018 --> 00:22:01.453 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: It would--
it started of for me,

00:22:01.453 --> 00:22:03.188 align:middle line:84%
all that I couldn't eat and
all the things that I didn't--

00:22:03.188 --> 00:22:06.325 align:middle line:84%
then I'll move to all of the
flowers that were as substitute

00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:07.926 align:middle line:84%
for those things and
then I just let it go

