00:34:53.858 --> 00:34:55.527 align:middle line:90%
I'm not a great cook at all.

00:34:55.527 --> 00:34:56.728 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:34:56.728 --> 00:34:58.096 align:middle line:84%
And so, would you
recommend to someone going in

00:34:58.096 --> 00:35:00.398 align:middle line:84%
and just clearing out their
entire refrigerator and starting

00:35:00.398 --> 00:35:01.666 align:middle line:90%
over again, all those--

00:35:01.666 --> 00:35:03.668 align:middle line:84%
old bottles of ketchup and
all of that jelly and--

00:35:03.668 --> 00:35:06.304 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I mean in an ideal
world that would be fantastic.

00:35:06.304 --> 00:35:09.574 align:middle line:84%
If you can do that and you
can just wipe it all out

00:35:09.574 --> 00:35:13.278 align:middle line:84%
and you can start over and
go buy everything new, great.

00:35:13.278 --> 00:35:14.946 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Would you
do bulk containers

00:35:14.946 --> 00:35:17.448 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I do use
glass jars, like this jar

00:35:17.448 --> 00:35:19.284 align:middle line:90%
