00:35:52.350 --> 00:35:54.519 align:middle line:84%
And then you build
your meals around--

00:35:54.519 --> 00:35:56.321 align:middle line:84%
you build around
plant-based eating

00:35:56.321 --> 00:35:57.422 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK.

00:35:57.422 --> 00:35:59.424 align:middle line:84%
All right now, let's
talk about kid's foods

00:35:59.424 --> 00:36:00.058 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:36:00.058 --> 00:36:00.925 align:middle line:90%
I want to go there

00:36:00.925 --> 00:36:02.393 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:36:02.393 --> 00:36:04.662 align:middle line:84%
I mean the kids lunch programs
in the schools completely suck.

00:36:04.662 --> 00:36:05.697 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Oh man.

00:36:05.697 --> 00:36:07.832 align:middle line:84%
There's a situation
with the kids food

00:36:07.832 --> 00:36:09.834 align:middle line:90%
and it really breaks my heart

00:36:09.834 --> 00:36:11.202 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: It does

00:36:11.202 --> 00:36:12.570 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Because when did
we come up with the concept

00:36:12.570 --> 00:36:15.306 align:middle line:84%
of kids food, that was
when it all fell apart.

00:36:15.306 --> 00:36:16.841 align:middle line:90%
What is kid's food?

00:36:16.841 --> 00:36:19.344 align:middle line:84%
Why did they now
have a whole genre?

00:36:19.344 --> 00:36:20.712 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Why is it different?

00:36:20.712 --> 00:36:21.946 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Why-- what is
going on with the kid's menu?

00:36:21.946 --> 00:36:23.047 align:middle line:90%
And you know what it is?

00:36:23.047 --> 00:36:26.117 align:middle line:84%
Its limited eating,
it's catering to a child

00:36:26.117 --> 00:36:30.154 align:middle line:84%
that doesn't have education and
it's not empowering to them.

00:36:30.154 --> 00:36:32.357 align:middle line:84%
And so, I don't believe in
kid's food, I don't believe

00:36:32.357 --> 00:36:37.362 align:middle line:84%
in hiding things in foods
either because what is that?

00:36:37.362 --> 00:36:39.030 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you're hiding
in the food

00:36:39.030 --> 00:36:42.267 align:middle line:84%
and then suddenly
they're 13 or 21--

00:36:42.267 --> 00:36:43.101 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:36:43.101 --> 00:36:44.502 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: -- or 25 or 35.

00:36:44.502 --> 00:36:45.637 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right.

00:36:45.637 --> 00:36:46.738 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: They don't
want to eat it when it's

00:36:46.738 --> 00:36:48.373 align:middle line:84%
in its natural form
because they never knew

00:36:48.373 --> 00:36:50.008 align:middle line:90%
that they ate it anyways.

00:36:50.008 --> 00:36:51.976 align:middle line:84%
So, you're really
creating a monster

00:36:51.976 --> 00:36:53.645 align:middle line:84%
and you're not doing
them any favor.

00:36:53.645 --> 00:36:54.946 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah.

00:36:54.946 --> 00:36:57.181 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: It's the old
school, this is what I cook,

00:36:57.181 --> 00:36:59.350 align:middle line:84%
this is what we're
having, I don't make a war.

00:36:59.350 --> 00:37:01.052 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe in battles.

00:37:01.052 --> 00:37:02.820 align:middle line:90%
And I'm not reactive to them.

00:37:02.820 --> 00:37:04.289 align:middle line:90%
Why would you get mad at them?

00:37:04.289 --> 00:37:05.957 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Well, right
but they say, well,

00:37:05.957 --> 00:37:08.893 align:middle line:84%
the kids will only pasta
and macaroni and cheese.

00:37:08.893 --> 00:37:11.162 align:middle line:84%
They won't eat the
spinach and the broccoli

00:37:11.162 --> 00:37:12.330 align:middle line:90%
if I put it around their plate

00:37:12.330 --> 00:37:13.298 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Right, well,

00:37:13.298 --> 00:37:14.499 align:middle line:84%
that's all that you've
given them.

00:37:14.499 --> 00:37:16.701 align:middle line:84%
So, first of all, you have
to take responsibility.

00:37:16.701 --> 00:37:18.569 align:middle line:84%
You got to own your
parenting shoes

00:37:18.569 --> 00:37:19.971 align:middle line:84%
and you got to say,
I'm the mama.

00:37:19.971 --> 00:37:21.372 align:middle line:90%
They don't have ATM card.

00:37:21.372 --> 00:37:22.674 align:middle line:90%
They don't have a car.

00:37:22.674 --> 00:37:25.276 align:middle line:84%
They don't drive and they
don't have any education.

00:37:25.276 --> 00:37:27.378 align:middle line:84%
So, why are they picking
what they're going to eat.

00:37:27.378 --> 00:37:30.581 align:middle line:84%
And so, you have to buck up,
you got to get in your kitchen.

00:37:30.581 --> 00:37:33.951 align:middle line:84%
You first have to eat and cook
and eat this way for you first

00:37:33.951 --> 00:37:35.153 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Right, and then--

00:37:35.153 --> 00:37:36.387 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Then once
you get good enough at it.

00:37:36.387 --> 00:37:37.655 align:middle line:90%
Start feeding them.

00:37:37.655 --> 00:37:38.990 align:middle line:90%
Start making the change.

00:37:38.990 --> 00:37:42.026 align:middle line:84%
Put a little on the plate and
you have to be consistent.

00:37:42.026 --> 00:37:43.728 align:middle line:90%
So, with color greens--

00:37:43.728 --> 00:37:47.598 align:middle line:84%
I love colors but my youngest
daughter wasn't having any part.

00:37:47.598 --> 00:37:48.800 align:middle line:90%
But I didn't make a war.

00:37:48.800 --> 00:37:51.836 align:middle line:84%
I'd put a little bit on
her plate twice a week.

00:37:51.836 --> 00:37:55.973 align:middle line:84%
Every week, twice a week, the
sauerkraut now they inhale it.

00:37:55.973 --> 00:37:59.777 align:middle line:84%
Every week on their plate,
there was sauerkraut.

00:37:59.777 --> 00:38:01.179 align:middle line:90%
They started to see it.

00:38:01.179 --> 00:38:02.847 align:middle line:84%
They formed a relationship
with it.

00:38:02.847 --> 00:38:03.614 align:middle line:90%
You have to take a bite.

00:38:03.614 --> 00:38:04.716 align:middle line:90%
You have to take one bite.

00:38:04.716 --> 00:38:05.717 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: That old school rule.

00:38:05.717 --> 00:38:06.517 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: That
they just try it.

00:38:06.517 --> 00:38:07.618 align:middle line:90%
They finally just tried it.

00:38:07.618 --> 00:38:09.287 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Yeah, just
try it, try it, try it.

00:38:09.287 --> 00:38:11.789 align:middle line:84%
I remember the day that Lola
[assumed spelling] was like,

00:38:11.789 --> 00:38:14.392 align:middle line:84%
"Mama, are we going
to have color green?

00:38:14.392 --> 00:38:19.597 align:middle line:84%
I was like-- and I thought
it worked, it worked.

00:38:19.597 --> 00:38:20.298 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Yeah.

00:38:20.298 --> 00:38:21.065 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: I'm a winner.

00:38:21.065 --> 00:38:22.133 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: That's good.

00:38:22.133 --> 00:38:23.134 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Do you have
any good suggestions

00:38:23.134 --> 00:38:23.968 align:middle line:84%
for lunch boxes or
kid's lunch boxes?

00:38:23.968 --> 00:38:24.936 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: I do, left over's

00:38:24.936 --> 00:38:26.571 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: That's a
good suggestion

00:38:26.571 --> 00:38:27.572 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And what
is that make you do?

00:38:27.572 --> 00:38:28.406 align:middle line:90%
It makes you cook.

00:38:28.406 --> 00:38:30.375 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: You got a point there.

00:38:30.375 --> 00:38:31.509 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:38:31.509 --> 00:38:32.910 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: You save
money, you cook dinner.

00:38:32.910 --> 00:38:38.516 align:middle line:84%
So, on Monday, we'll-- maybe I
do make them chicken fingers--

00:38:38.516 --> 00:38:39.617 align:middle line:90%
my version.

00:38:39.617 --> 00:38:41.686 align:middle line:84%
It's a minor-- its
organic chicken,

00:38:41.686 --> 00:38:44.155 align:middle line:90%
its almond meal encrusted.

00:38:44.155 --> 00:38:45.456 align:middle line:90%
I'll make them on Friday.

00:38:45.456 --> 00:38:49.761 align:middle line:84%
That's their treat dinner
and maybe I'll do, you know,

00:38:49.761 --> 00:38:50.995 align:middle line:90%
some kind of steamed broccolis.

00:38:50.995 --> 00:38:53.865 align:middle line:84%
Steamed broccoli the next
day is fantastic cold.

00:38:53.865 --> 00:38:55.066 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: And you put
them on lunch box?

00:38:55.066 --> 00:38:56.667 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I put in the
lunch containers, Yeah.

00:38:56.667 --> 00:38:57.702 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah

00:38:57.702 --> 00:38:58.469 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: And
then they have that.

00:38:58.469 --> 00:38:59.637 align:middle line:90%
And then they have fruit.

00:38:59.637 --> 00:39:00.405 align:middle line:90%
They're good

00:39:00.405 --> 00:39:01.773 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah

00:39:01.773 --> 00:39:03.408 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: So, leftovers
are the beans, the grains,

00:39:03.408 --> 00:39:06.144 align:middle line:84%
turned into burritos,
rice is fantastic.

00:39:06.144 --> 00:39:08.279 align:middle line:84%
Heat it up in the morning,
put it in a thermos.

00:39:08.279 --> 00:39:10.815 align:middle line:84%
Soups are wonderful
on a thermos.

00:39:10.815 --> 00:39:12.083 align:middle line:90%
Salads are super easy.

