00:39:20.224 --> 00:39:22.527 align:middle line:84%
with the home made
dressing in a container.

00:39:22.527 --> 00:39:23.194 align:middle line:90%
>>Lisa: Wow.

00:39:23.194 --> 00:39:23.895 align:middle line:90%
>> McCormick: Real.

00:39:23.895 --> 00:39:26.097 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: That's great.

00:39:26.097 --> 00:39:26.964 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: They're
eating real food.

00:39:26.964 --> 00:39:28.399 align:middle line:90%
And it wasn't a conversation.

00:39:28.399 --> 00:39:29.667 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: Yup, it
wasn't a conversation.

00:39:29.667 --> 00:39:30.868 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:39:30.868 --> 00:39:32.470 align:middle line:84%
So, you have done the same
thing with kitchens all

00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:34.972 align:middle line:84%
around the place where you
have these food kitchens.

00:39:34.972 --> 00:39:37.108 align:middle line:84%
What are they and we have a
picture here of one of your--

00:39:37.108 --> 00:39:39.410 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Yeah,
they're community kitchens.

00:39:39.410 --> 00:39:40.478 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: OK

00:39:40.478 --> 00:39:42.046 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: I-- when
I was getting well

00:39:42.046 --> 00:39:45.116 align:middle line:84%
and I was still very
sick, that 89-pound girl.

00:39:45.116 --> 00:39:49.887 align:middle line:84%
I had a moment where I
thought, oh wow, I don't want

00:39:49.887 --> 00:39:51.823 align:middle line:90%
to tell people what to do.

00:39:51.823 --> 00:39:53.524 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to show
them what I do.

00:39:53.524 --> 00:39:54.625 align:middle line:90%
>> Lisa: Yeah

00:39:54.625 --> 00:39:55.827 align:middle line:84%
>> McCormick: Because
if you tell people,

00:39:55.827 --> 00:39:57.695 align:middle line:84%
then you're pointing a
finger and no one listens.

00:39:57.695 --> 00:40:01.098 align:middle line:84%
But I thought if I just go in
to my community in Nashville

00:40:01.098 --> 00:40:03.801 align:middle line:84%
and I set up shop, let
me show some people.

00:40:03.801 --> 00:40:06.704 align:middle line:84%
So, I went into a
food desert just

00:40:06.704 --> 00:40:07.738 align:middle line:90%
like the neighborhood I grew

00:40:07.738 --> 00:40:10.141 align:middle line:84%
up in predominantly
African-American.

00:40:10.141 --> 00:40:13.744 align:middle line:84%
And I connected with the
church and I went in.

00:40:13.744 --> 00:40:16.581 align:middle line:84%
And I would stand there at
89 pounds and I'm bragging

00:40:16.581 --> 00:40:18.916 align:middle line:84%
about myself because
I'm proud of that girl.

00:40:18.916 --> 00:40:22.520 align:middle line:84%
And I would stand there and
I would make tofu, schnitzel,

00:40:22.520 --> 00:40:26.624 align:middle line:84%
and anything I could come up
with that I could try to make.

00:40:26.624 --> 00:40:29.694 align:middle line:84%
And I would cook for 40 and 50
people for a dollar a person.

00:40:29.694 --> 00:40:32.630 align:middle line:84%
And then eventually the
congregation would come

00:40:32.630 --> 00:40:34.999 align:middle line:90%
in people started helping me.

00:40:34.999 --> 00:40:38.002 align:middle line:84%
And then people in the city
of Nashville heard about me.

00:40:38.002 --> 00:40:41.405 align:middle line:84%
And they would come and I was
cooking on the morning show

00:40:41.405 --> 00:40:43.007 align:middle line:90%
and I'd stand and cook.

00:40:43.007 --> 00:40:45.176 align:middle line:84%
And I'd talk to these
kids and the families.

00:40:45.176 --> 00:40:47.578 align:middle line:84%
And I go out in the street
and round up people to eat

00:40:47.578 --> 00:40:49.814 align:middle line:84%
because they don't have any
food when they're hungry.

00:40:49.814 --> 00:40:51.749 align:middle line:84%
They couldn't just get
a free meal they had

00:40:51.749 --> 00:40:52.783 align:middle line:90%
to learn to cook it.

00:40:52.783 --> 00:40:54.552 align:middle line:84%
>> Lisa: They did,
God, its beautiful.

